The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Burdwan, April 23: Students of a high school in Burdwans Bhatar ransacked classrooms today after teachers refused to start classes earlier because of the heat.     
	The government had on Thursday issued a circular asking schools to change their schedule for students relief. In Burdwan, the maximum today touched 41 degrees Celsius. But Susundighi H.P. High School, about 140km from Calcutta, refused to budge after some of its teachers said they could not come as early as 7am.        
	Asansol: Police on Friday claimed to have found CDs showing scenes from Maoist training camps from the house of Samir Biswas, a doctor wanted for alleged guerrilla links. The doctors arrested help, Susanta Pal, is said to have told the police Maoists had held 10 meetings in his attic.        
	Calcutta: The state will recruit 500 cops to strengthen the security of the eight people here who get Z or Z plus cover. Among them are the chief minister, governor, Pranab Mukherjee and Mamata Banerjee.                                                                                                                                                      
